{% comment %}
Meal Plan — full view.
merge_variables come from server/src/services/trmnlService.ts:
  days: [{ date, dayName, formattedDate, meals: string[], mealCount, isToday }]
  totalDays, totalMeals
Only today and future days are ever sent — past days are filtered server-side.

.layout defaults to flex-direction: row, so layout--col is required here —
without it every day's label and meal grid lay out side by side instead of
stacking. .columns/.column is a fixed side-by-side panel component (like a
2-up page split), not a repeatable per-item header, so the day label is a
plain .label sibling of its .grid instead.

layout--top would center the cross-axis on a layout--col (it's meant for
row layouts), leaving the day label centered above a left-aligned grid —
layout--align-start/layout--justify-start set each axis independently, so
both the label and the grid sit flush left, top to bottom.
{% endcomment %}
<div class="layout layout--col layout--align-start layout--justify-start">
  {% for day in days limit:7 %}
    <span class="label label--underline">{{ day.dayName }}</span>

    <div class="grid grid--cols-1 gap--xsmall">
      {% if day.meals.size > 0 %}
        {% for meal in day.meals %}
          <div class="item">
            <div class="meta">
              <span class="index">{{ forloop.index }}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="content">
              <span class="title title--small" data-clamp="1">{{ meal }}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        {% endfor %}
      {% else %}
        <div class="item">
          <div class="content">
            <span class="description">Inga måltider planerade</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

<div class="title_bar">
  <span class="title">Matsedel</span>
  <span class="instance">{{ totalMeals }} måltider · {{ totalDays }} dagar framåt</span>
</div>
